HEADWORD: Forelay
<hw>Fore*lay"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
lay down beforehand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These grounds being <qex>forelaid</qex> and understood.</q>
<rj><qau>Mede.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To waylay. See <er>Forlay</er>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foreleader</ent>⟦br⟧
